custgwttbl.client
Class CustGwtDataHolder

java.lang.Object
  custgwttbl.client.CustGwtDataHolder

public class CustGwtDataHolder
extends java.lang.Object

This holds the data to transfer . This is a serialized object. All explanations are based on the generic rpc servlet CustGwtDataServiceImpl. If you use your own rpc servlet then you can set parameters as your requirement, but the return values should be always ArrayList of ArrayList, if it is fetching data set for displaying in the grid

setParamAndValues

public void setParamAndValues(java.lang.String newParamAndValues)
Sets param and value list for the rpc call. If the generic rpc servlet is called it expects the following format paramName|paramValue|paramDataType~paramName|paramValue|paramDataType... paramName can be anything, but the value should be in exact sequence as your prepared statement which is set by calling method setPreparedStatementSQL(String newPreparedStatementSQL). View the generic rpc CustGwtDataServiceImpl.

Parameters:
newParamAndValues - name and value list

setPreparedStatementSQL

public void setPreparedStatementSQL(java.lang.String newPreparedStatementSQL)
Sets prepared statement sql for execution. e.g select a, b, c from xyz where z=? and s=? and userid=?. Then your argument for setParamAndValues(String newParamAndValues) will be like below, z|5|number~s|hello|varchar~userid|23|number

Parameters:
newPreparedStatementSQL - prepared statement sql
